item.title: How to make a button on interface bring website up?
item.dc:creator: @chassy13 Chassy13
item.description:
@chassy13 wrote:

I am not positive if it would work, but try something like this:

public static void browse(String url) { String browserPath = ""; browserPath = "C:/Program Files/Internet Explorer/iexplore.exe"; try { String[] b = {browserPath, url}; Runtime.getRuntime().exec(b); } catch (Exception exc) { exc.printStackTrace(); } }

And then inside the designated packet,

browse("www.website.com");

Note: You need to do the rest if you want other browsers that aren’t Internet Explorer.
